{
  "texts": [
    "In this trial, the TurtleBot2 navigated a narrow corridor with an L-shaped obstacle configuration.",
    "The robot first entered the L-shape region and then made active turns to navigate out of the region and continue toward the goal.",
    "This shows that X-Nav can overcome concave obstacles with active exploration.",
    "A video of X-Nav and the supplementary material are provided at our project webpage: https://cross-embodiment-nav.github.io.TABLE II: ABLATION STUDY Variants Go2 Jackal SR SPL SR SPL X-Nav w L1 54.2 0.41 85.7 0.77 Offline BC 65.3 0.57 86.3 0.80 X-Nav w EC 40.5 0.37 87.2 0.79 X-Nav w/o TE 69.5 0.61 76.3 0.68 X-Nav w TE 43.3 0.36 88.3 0.82 X-Nav 69.5 0.61 88.3 0.82 Jackal with ZED 2 Camera (a) (b) TurtleBot2 with Kinect Camera Table III: REAL-WORLD EXPERIMENTS SR SPL ViNT 70 0.63 NavDP 65 0.60 X-Nav 80 0.71 Fig. 9.",
    "An example of X-Nav overcoming local minima in a real-world experiment."
